WEBVTT

00:11.041 --> 00:13.125
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.125 --> 00:15.625
I'll give you the phone
for a piece of your NFL deal.

00:15.625 --> 00:17.417
- How much?
- 5%.

00:17.417 --> 00:18.417
2.5%.

00:18.417 --> 00:19.750
3%.

00:19.750 --> 00:21.917
Done.
Congratulations.

00:21.917 --> 00:23.625
You wanted a football team.
You bought it.

00:23.625 --> 00:26.291
- Ray, you're smiling.
- Must be contagious.

00:26.291 --> 00:27.458
- I shot him.
- You shot who?

00:27.458 --> 00:28.959
My abuser.

00:28.959 --> 00:33.333
I shot him in the stomach,
and Ray shot him in the head.

00:33.333 --> 00:34.583
[gunshot]

00:34.583 --> 00:36.375
Thank you for telling me that.

00:36.375 --> 00:37.458
You like him.

00:37.458 --> 00:38.750
- Who?
- Donellen.

00:38.750 --> 00:39.750
What are you looking at?

00:39.750 --> 00:41.291
This is Marvin.

00:41.291 --> 00:43.333
- He was my boyfriend.
- Sarah.

00:45.667 --> 00:50.375
I was wondering if maybe we
could buy the bar from my dad.

00:50.375 --> 00:51.959
I don't see why not.

00:51.959 --> 00:53.041
[Terry]
You see him, Ray?

00:53.041 --> 00:54.125
- See who?
- Get down!

00:54.125 --> 00:55.834
[gunshots]

00:55.834 --> 00:56.959
What the fuck are you doing?

00:56.959 --> 00:58.834
It's just the Parkinson's,
Terry.

00:58.834 --> 01:00.333
Doctor said
this could happen.

01:00.333 --> 01:03.250
Hi, I'm Helen Miller,
Fish and Game.

01:03.250 --> 01:06.166
She is gonna fix
the bird situation at the field.

01:06.166 --> 01:09.750
No governor, no stadium.
No stadium, no football.

01:09.750 --> 01:11.875
We are now projecting
that Meg Townsend

01:11.875 --> 01:14.750
will be the first female
governor of California.

01:14.750 --> 01:16.000
Fucking governor lost.

01:16.000 --> 01:18.041
3%, huh, Paige?

01:18.041 --> 01:19.917
I'm so disappointed
in you, Ray.

01:19.917 --> 01:21.834
I mean,
you didn't think I'd find out?

01:21.834 --> 01:24.375
She got what she wanted,

01:24.375 --> 01:27.542
and you got 3%
of fucking nothing.

01:29.041 --> 01:30.417
Good night, Ray.

01:30.417 --> 01:33.625
What are you doing
with those people, Ray?

01:44.667 --> 01:47.542
[birds chirping]

01:51.333 --> 01:54.375
[pensive music playing]

01:54.375 --> 01:57.083
♪♪♪

01:57.083 --> 01:59.083
[clicking tongue]

01:59.083 --> 02:00.375
[whistling]

02:08.208 --> 02:13.291
♪♪♪

02:32.917 --> 02:35.083
[doorbell chimes]

02:43.792 --> 02:45.041
Are the papers in order?

02:45.041 --> 02:47.291
- Yes.
- Great, he's upstairs.

02:50.166 --> 02:53.000
[woman on PA] Nurse Grand
to oncology three, please.

02:53.000 --> 02:55.792
Nurse Grand to oncology three.

02:55.792 --> 02:57.959
You all right?

02:57.959 --> 03:01.917
I'm not seeing fucking Aryans,
if that's what you're asking.

03:01.917 --> 03:04.000
I don't sleep much.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.166
What, restlessness, insomnia?

03:07.166 --> 03:10.959
It's like I'm having dreams
when I'm awake.

03:10.959 --> 03:12.625
Other day,
I'm lying in my bed,

03:12.625 --> 03:16.333
and suddenly my clothes start
fucking walking around the room.

03:16.333 --> 03:17.834
[chuckles]

03:17.834 --> 03:19.625
- What's funny?
- Nothing, nothing.

03:19.625 --> 03:22.250
Just another symptom
we can manage with medication.

03:22.250 --> 03:23.750
Yeah, well,
it's not fucking funny.

03:23.750 --> 03:26.083
No, of course it's not.

03:26.083 --> 03:27.959
We'll change your medication,

03:27.959 --> 03:30.709
and we'll start you off
on some occupational therapy.

03:30.709 --> 03:32.667
Sounds like a plan.

03:35.250 --> 03:38.500
[Dr. Righellis] So tell me,
where are you living now?

03:38.500 --> 03:39.500
In my gym.

03:39.500 --> 03:41.166
And you have assistance there?

03:41.166 --> 03:43.959
Yeah, I got a guy
who helps me with the fighters.

03:43.959 --> 03:46.542
No, no, I'm not talking
about help with your job,

03:46.542 --> 03:48.208
I mean
someone with medical training

03:48.208 --> 03:51.000
to help you
with your daily needs.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.458
No, I don't need
nobody like that.

03:53.458 --> 03:56.667
Parkinson's follows
a predictable course.

03:56.667 --> 03:58.583
This is the time
we start talking to patients

03:58.583 --> 04:01.500
about in-home support.

04:01.500 --> 04:05.166
Living alone isn't going to be
your best option.

04:08.500 --> 04:10.250
[exhales]

04:13.875 --> 04:16.709
[light rock music playing]

04:16.709 --> 04:21.792
♪♪♪

04:27.792 --> 04:29.917
[engine turns over]

04:29.917 --> 04:32.500
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

04:32.500 --> 04:34.291
[horn honks]

04:34.291 --> 04:36.250
You motherfuckers!

04:36.250 --> 04:39.250
- My Caddy!
- What happened?

04:39.250 --> 04:42.375
[spits] The fucking Armenians
came over to collect, Pop.

04:42.375 --> 04:44.208
Came in the house with a gun,
put it in my face,

04:44.208 --> 04:45.375
and pistol-whipped me.

04:45.375 --> 04:46.583
How much are they after?

04:46.583 --> 04:48.500
$30,000.

04:48.500 --> 04:51.208
Pop, you said this whole
title thing was a formality,

04:51.208 --> 04:53.041
that they wouldn't take my car!

04:53.041 --> 04:54.166
I'm sorry, kiddo.

04:54.166 --> 04:56.166
Get collecting from the girls.

04:56.166 --> 04:58.333
I'm sure this is all
a big fucking misunderstanding.

04:59.750 --> 05:02.250
$30,000?

05:03.250 --> 05:05.417
[sirens wailing]

05:05.417 --> 05:08.583
[muffled hip-hop music plays
on the stereo]

05:08.583 --> 05:13.417
♪♪♪

05:19.709 --> 05:20.917
My shorts.

05:22.792 --> 05:26.291
Nobody wants to see
a grown man wearing these.

05:26.291 --> 05:28.250
Besides, your legs
are too skinny.

05:29.750 --> 05:31.583
You gonna give that
to charity?

05:31.583 --> 05:34.542
Gonna give it
to the garbageman.

05:56.542 --> 05:58.625
Oh, this is pretty.

05:58.625 --> 06:00.542
[Teresa]
It's for my big brother.

06:00.542 --> 06:02.959
He died
before I was born.

06:04.792 --> 06:06.959
Huh.

06:06.959 --> 06:10.000
What's with the dead bird?

06:10.000 --> 06:12.125
His life flew away.

06:33.542 --> 06:36.291
Can I talk to you a sec?

06:36.291 --> 06:38.333
Sure.

06:49.041 --> 06:50.667
You saw that woman?

06:50.667 --> 06:51.709
Yeah.

06:51.709 --> 06:55.500
Yeah.
She's gonna be my wife.

06:58.000 --> 06:59.709
Yeah?

06:59.709 --> 07:03.208
I'm gonna need
my settlement money now.

07:03.208 --> 07:05.000
We need to go talk
to that lawyer again.

07:05.000 --> 07:06.709
Look, slow the fuck down,
Bunch.

07:06.709 --> 07:09.709
- It's my settlement.
- Okay.

07:09.709 --> 07:11.959
- How long have you known her?
- What does it matter, Ray?

07:11.959 --> 07:15.166
I love her,
and I want my money.

07:15.166 --> 07:16.750
I'm not signing over
all that money

07:16.750 --> 07:18.709
just so you can give it
to somebody you just met, Bunch.

07:18.709 --> 07:22.125
I'm the one who stood up
in front of the fucking world

07:22.125 --> 07:25.208
and admitted
what happened to me.

07:25.208 --> 07:27.083
You didn't do that.

07:31.375 --> 07:34.458
No, I didn't.

07:34.458 --> 07:37.166
Well, I'm gonna expect you
to transfer the account

07:37.166 --> 07:40.583
to my name this week.

07:42.375 --> 07:44.917
So I spoke
to your sister about the bar,

07:44.917 --> 07:49.041
went over the particulars,
inventory, furniture, fixtures,

07:49.041 --> 07:50.250
and tax returns.

07:50.250 --> 07:52.417
- Great.
- If you say so.

07:52.417 --> 07:54.083
Place is a fucking money pit.

07:54.083 --> 07:56.583
Hasn't turned a profit
in 12 years.

07:56.583 --> 07:59.417
It's not about profit.
It's about family.

07:59.417 --> 08:01.083
You know,
most wives want a shop

08:01.083 --> 08:04.417
where they can sell soap
or that type of shit.

08:04.417 --> 08:07.375
You want a dive
in South Boston.

08:07.375 --> 08:09.208
Ah, whatever keeps it fresh
at home.

08:09.208 --> 08:11.917
Can we just get this over with?

08:11.917 --> 08:13.417
Fine.

08:13.417 --> 08:15.709
Ray needs to come up
with $375,000,

08:15.709 --> 08:19.250
and then you win some kind
of sister-of-the-year award.

08:19.250 --> 08:20.375
Oh, thank God
you're here.

08:20.375 --> 08:22.125
- Harriet.
- Hey.

08:22.125 --> 08:24.458
We're just going over
the papers for my dad's place.

08:24.458 --> 08:27.458
[dog barking in the distance]

08:27.458 --> 08:31.375
Haven't changed your mind,
have you?

08:31.375 --> 08:33.333
No.

08:33.333 --> 08:37.125
[Abby] So you're okay with me
going forward with this?

08:37.125 --> 08:38.375
Sure.

08:38.375 --> 08:40.125
Everything in order,
Harriet?

08:40.125 --> 08:43.375
Massachusetts is not gonna
do much for you tax-wise.

08:43.375 --> 08:44.709
Get it done.

08:44.709 --> 08:47.625
[dog continues barking]

08:54.750 --> 08:57.709
[door creaks]

08:57.709 --> 09:00.750
[gentle music playing]

09:00.750 --> 09:04.667
♪♪♪

09:04.667 --> 09:07.000
[exhales]

09:09.667 --> 09:11.500
[grunts]

09:21.166 --> 09:24.333
[typing]

09:24.333 --> 09:25.333
[dialing]

09:25.333 --> 09:26.500
[phone line rings]

09:26.500 --> 09:30.166
[phone rings]

09:30.166 --> 09:31.709
[Paige]
Ray?

09:31.709 --> 09:33.083
[Ray] We can still make
that property work.

09:33.083 --> 09:34.709
It's fucking over.

09:34.709 --> 09:36.417
Without Verona,
we can't budge Fish and Game.

09:36.417 --> 09:38.250
We can't force the sale
of the apartments.

09:38.250 --> 09:40.875
How quickly can you put
together $200,000 in cash?

09:40.875 --> 09:42.750
- Why?
- Can you do it?

09:42.750 --> 09:44.709
Yes.

09:44.709 --> 09:46.709
Call me when it's done.

09:51.166 --> 09:53.041
[Abby]
Ray?

09:58.542 --> 10:01.667
You know they'd have lost
the bar without you.

10:01.667 --> 10:02.625
Thank you.

10:06.875 --> 10:08.625
What are you doing
sitting in here?

10:11.166 --> 10:15.709
I, uh, took Terry
to a specialist today.

10:15.709 --> 10:17.583
And?

10:17.583 --> 10:21.166
He's getting worse.

10:21.166 --> 10:23.458
I think he should move in here
with us.

10:27.083 --> 10:29.333
Okay.

10:29.333 --> 10:31.583
Has Terry agreed to that?

10:31.583 --> 10:34.917
I haven't told him yet.

10:40.583 --> 10:43.458
[engine revs]

10:43.458 --> 10:46.291
Hey. Hey!

10:46.291 --> 10:48.041
- Yo!
- [engine starts]

10:48.041 --> 10:49.083
Hey, give me my ca...

10:49.083 --> 10:52.083
[tires squealing]

10:52.083 --> 10:53.917
Fuck you!

10:56.834 --> 10:58.208
What the fuck?

10:58.208 --> 10:59.750
What happened?
You guys okay?

10:59.750 --> 11:01.291
That little guy
shook us down.

11:01.291 --> 11:04.083
He took the money?

11:15.834 --> 11:17.000
We're not there yet.

11:17.000 --> 11:19.125
You sure about that?

11:21.250 --> 11:22.125
Bunchy's getting married.

11:22.125 --> 11:23.667
What?

11:23.667 --> 11:26.583
To who?

11:26.583 --> 11:30.625
I don't know her name,
some Mexican wrestler.

11:30.625 --> 11:33.083
Jesus Christ,
she works fast.

11:33.083 --> 11:36.250
He's gonna get
his heart broke.

11:36.250 --> 11:38.125
Ray, come on.

11:38.125 --> 11:40.959
[phone ringing]

11:44.500 --> 11:47.083
[clears throat]

11:47.083 --> 11:49.125
Yeah.

11:49.125 --> 11:50.500
- I have the money.
- Where are you?

11:50.500 --> 11:52.125
My father's plant.

11:52.125 --> 11:55.000
Don't move.

11:57.166 --> 11:58.000
Who was that?

11:59.500 --> 12:02.333
Work.

12:02.333 --> 12:04.250
Go ahead.

12:04.250 --> 12:05.583
I got this.

12:11.583 --> 12:14.333
I'd never even heard
of Calabasas before I met you.

12:14.333 --> 12:15.083
It's not so bad.

12:15.083 --> 12:17.000
Anyone home?

12:17.000 --> 12:19.792
It's so far away; it's like
I'm on vacation or something.

12:19.792 --> 12:23.500
[laughter]

12:23.500 --> 12:25.000
Got anything to drink?

12:25.000 --> 12:28.625
Um, Coke,
maybe some lemonade.

12:28.625 --> 12:31.041
Something to drink, drink.

12:33.000 --> 12:37.041
Sure. Sure.

12:37.041 --> 12:39.041
[pop music plays on the stereo]

12:39.041 --> 12:41.125
♪ It's like the sun coming
After the rain ♪

12:41.125 --> 12:42.250
♪ It's like... ♪

12:42.250 --> 12:44.583
I've got a surprise
for you.

12:44.583 --> 12:45.542
What?

12:45.542 --> 12:49.166
Go on Facebook.

12:49.166 --> 12:51.125
Type in Sarah Donellen.

12:51.125 --> 12:53.041
- What?
- Do it.

13:00.250 --> 13:02.792
He didn't take down
her Facebook page.

13:04.291 --> 13:06.166
This is so creepy.

13:06.166 --> 13:08.375
Check this out.

13:09.875 --> 13:11.667
- Oh, my God.
- What?

13:11.667 --> 13:14.333
She died in Sayulita.

13:14.333 --> 13:16.208
That's so sad.

13:16.208 --> 13:20.583
♪♪♪

13:20.583 --> 13:22.000
[exhales]

13:26.375 --> 13:29.250
[birds squawking]

13:42.583 --> 13:44.875
That's called murmuration.

13:44.875 --> 13:48.750
It only takes a single bird
making the slightest shift

13:48.750 --> 13:52.291
in course to move
the entire flock.

13:56.041 --> 13:58.125
You all right?

14:03.625 --> 14:05.959
Fucking tip-top.
Here's the $200,000.

14:08.250 --> 14:11.375
What's it for?

14:11.375 --> 14:12.750
Fish and Game lady.

14:12.750 --> 14:14.166
Well,
even if she takes the money,

14:14.166 --> 14:17.792
Napier's demanding $90 million
for those apartments.

14:17.792 --> 14:19.375
My father's never gonna pay
for that.

14:19.375 --> 14:22.250
I'm gonna go see Helen Miller.

14:22.250 --> 14:23.834
Sort out Napier next.

14:23.834 --> 14:26.959
Ray.

14:26.959 --> 14:29.542
I served Varick with
divorce papers this morning.

14:29.542 --> 14:31.542
Is that gonna cause problems?

14:31.542 --> 14:34.959
[chuckles]
Of all kinds.

14:44.959 --> 14:47.000
[phone ringing in the distance]

14:49.166 --> 14:50.500
Oh, hello.

14:50.500 --> 14:51.542
I'm Helen Miller.

14:51.542 --> 14:53.875
Ray Donovan.

14:56.583 --> 14:58.000
Oh.

14:58.000 --> 15:01.667
Yeah, we met at the, uh,
the governor's party.

15:01.667 --> 15:03.458
Yeah,
you're Andrew Finney's man.

15:03.458 --> 15:05.000
Right.

15:09.291 --> 15:11.208
What's this?

15:11.208 --> 15:13.458
The Finney family
would like to make a donation

15:13.458 --> 15:15.917
to the California Aviary
Project.

15:15.917 --> 15:20.208
Well, I have never heard
of such an organization.

15:20.208 --> 15:22.875
Its chief concern
is the preservation

15:22.875 --> 15:26.125
of the tricolored blackbird.

15:29.875 --> 15:31.375
Are you bribing me?

15:31.375 --> 15:32.917
Open it.

15:47.166 --> 15:50.959
Mr. Donovan, the nesting site
of the blackbird

15:50.959 --> 15:52.834
is protected by statutes.

15:52.834 --> 15:54.542
The family
was hoping your commission

15:54.542 --> 15:56.458
could help find the birds
a new place to nest.

15:56.458 --> 15:58.000
The Agelaius Tricolor

15:58.000 --> 16:00.375
is a bird of very specific
migratory patterns.

16:00.375 --> 16:01.917
Sure.

16:01.917 --> 16:03.500
They've been nesting
at that Redondo plant

16:03.500 --> 16:04.959
for over 60 years.

16:04.959 --> 16:06.208
Have you seen the plant,
Helen?

16:06.208 --> 16:07.875
It's a shithole.

16:07.875 --> 16:10.417
I'm sure those birds
would be happy for a change.

16:15.291 --> 16:17.959
Well,

16:17.959 --> 16:21.250
it is a very nice bag.

16:24.125 --> 16:25.542
I'll be in touch.

16:25.542 --> 16:27.750
That won't be necessary.

16:27.750 --> 16:30.458
Enjoy the bag.

16:33.542 --> 16:35.333
Helen Miller signed off.

16:35.333 --> 16:36.375
[Paige]
What?

16:36.375 --> 16:37.875
That's amazing.

16:37.875 --> 16:39.250
She should have
the paperwork filed

16:39.250 --> 16:41.041
by the end of the week.

16:41.041 --> 16:45.166
I'll call you
when I got a line on Napier.

16:45.166 --> 16:46.375
You there?

16:46.375 --> 16:49.542
I have to call you back.

16:49.542 --> 16:51.542
You can't do this.

16:51.542 --> 16:54.208
It's over, Varick.

16:55.834 --> 16:57.709
This isn't gonna
go over well.

16:57.709 --> 16:59.291
I want you out by tonight.

16:59.291 --> 17:01.375
Look, you're tired,
and you're upset.

17:01.375 --> 17:03.750
No, I want you
out of here by tonight.

17:03.750 --> 17:05.625
I'll go to a hotel
for a few nights and--

17:05.625 --> 17:06.667
till you calm down.

17:06.667 --> 17:08.500
I don't need to calm down,

17:08.500 --> 17:13.041
and a few days in a hotel isn't
gonna change a fucking thing.

17:15.625 --> 17:17.291
Could...

17:38.834 --> 17:42.917
[strums guitar]

17:50.625 --> 17:53.500
[lightly strumming]

17:55.834 --> 17:57.917
[door clicks open]

18:01.500 --> 18:04.166
[Daryll]
Hey, where'd you go, Pop?

18:06.041 --> 18:07.458
You straighten
everything out?

18:07.458 --> 18:11.875
Working on it.

18:11.875 --> 18:14.041
Davros, I got the money.

18:14.041 --> 18:16.792
Where should we meet?

18:16.792 --> 18:18.917
Fine, I'll be there.

18:20.709 --> 18:22.333
You got the money?

18:22.333 --> 18:24.083
Sure.

18:24.083 --> 18:26.875
From where?

18:26.875 --> 18:29.375
I'm a resourceful person.

18:32.083 --> 18:34.208
What is this?

18:35.041 --> 18:36.709
We got a plumbing problem?

18:36.709 --> 18:38.709
So to speak.

18:38.709 --> 18:39.917
Where's Audrey?

18:39.917 --> 18:41.000
We were in the middle of a game.

18:41.000 --> 18:43.542
Not anymore.
Little kid wiped me out.

18:58.083 --> 18:59.083
I need you
to figure out an angle

18:59.083 --> 19:00.458
on a guy
named Roger Napier.

19:00.458 --> 19:02.083
What do you want him to do?

19:02.083 --> 19:03.750
Let go of a piece of property
he's holding.

19:03.750 --> 19:07.875
[phone rings]

19:07.875 --> 19:09.667
- Raymond Donovan?
- Yeah.

19:09.667 --> 19:10.959
My name is Thomas Romero.

19:10.959 --> 19:12.834
I spoke
with your brother Brendan

19:12.834 --> 19:16.083
about the murder
of Father Daniel O'Connor.

19:16.083 --> 19:19.917
[birds cooing]

19:19.917 --> 19:23.333
Mr. Donovan,
are you there?

19:25.750 --> 19:27.917
I need to speak with you
in person.

19:27.917 --> 19:30.208
I'll send you an address.

19:38.834 --> 19:40.375
Fuck.

19:41.792 --> 19:43.458
Oh, fuck.

19:45.166 --> 19:47.625
- Yeah.
- Forget about Napier.

19:47.625 --> 19:49.750
I need you to look
into something else for me.

19:49.750 --> 19:52.625
All I got's a name.

19:56.542 --> 20:00.291
[muffled music plays
on the stereo]

20:00.291 --> 20:02.166
We got to talk.

20:02.166 --> 20:04.625
- What's wrong?
- In the office, now.

20:14.125 --> 20:17.959
Who the fuck is Thomas Romero?

20:17.959 --> 20:19.083
He's a friend of mine.

20:19.083 --> 20:21.375
Yeah?
How do you know him?

20:21.375 --> 20:23.250
He comes to SNAP.

20:25.291 --> 20:28.208
Did you talk to him
about O'Connor?

20:28.208 --> 20:30.166
What? No.

20:30.166 --> 20:31.542
No?

20:31.542 --> 20:34.875
So why is he calling me
asking about a murder?

20:36.667 --> 20:39.208
Thomas is a SNAP guy.
He was abused too.

20:39.208 --> 20:41.333
What did you tell him
about Father O'Connor, Bunch?

20:41.333 --> 20:42.750
I never said that name.

20:42.750 --> 20:45.917
Tell me exactly
what you fucking said.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.667
It's hard to remember.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.375
Well, you better
fucking remember.

21:02.500 --> 21:04.542
I guess I...

21:06.542 --> 21:08.834
I told him that I shot him
in the stomach,

21:08.834 --> 21:11.417
and you shot him in the head.

21:11.417 --> 21:13.875
You fucking idiot.
You fucking idiot!

21:13.875 --> 21:15.250
- You ratted your brother!
- Hey, all right, all right.

21:15.250 --> 21:16.542
You ratted
your fucking brother!

21:16.542 --> 21:18.375
You have any idea
what you've done?

21:18.375 --> 21:19.458
- I didn't rat on nobody!
- Calm down. All right.

21:19.458 --> 21:20.500
- Yeah?
- He's a friend of mine!

21:20.500 --> 21:22.875
Yeah, the fuck he is!

21:22.875 --> 21:24.750
You get it now, Bunch,

21:24.750 --> 21:26.333
why Ray can't let you
have that money?

21:26.333 --> 21:28.875
Why we can't let you marry
that fucking Mexican?

21:28.875 --> 21:30.250
[grunts]

21:30.250 --> 21:32.375
Jesus fucking Christ,
what are you doing?

21:32.375 --> 21:34.917
- You don't say that!
- You can't fucking hit him!

21:40.417 --> 21:41.917
- You all right?
- [exhales]

21:41.917 --> 21:45.000
[phone rings]

21:49.375 --> 21:50.583
Yeah.

21:50.583 --> 21:52.583
Thomas Romero's
a priest, Ray.

21:53.750 --> 21:55.583
- What?
- Yeah.

21:55.583 --> 21:57.625
He runs something called
the Servants of Paraclete.

21:57.625 --> 22:01.000
It's where the Catholic Church
sends their child molesters.

22:01.000 --> 22:02.542
Are you fucking kidding me?

22:02.542 --> 22:05.083
No, he's 51,
he's been there for 15 years,

22:05.083 --> 22:07.500
and before that,
he was in Baltimore.

22:07.500 --> 22:09.500
That's all I got.

22:13.959 --> 22:15.375
Jesus.

22:17.417 --> 22:20.375
[scoffs]

22:20.375 --> 22:22.333
Your SNAP friend was sent
by the Catholic Church.

22:22.333 --> 22:24.458
Oh, fuck.

22:25.458 --> 22:27.125
What?

22:27.125 --> 22:29.458
He's a priest.

22:31.500 --> 22:33.250
Thomas is a priest?

22:33.250 --> 22:35.208
What are we gonna do?

22:37.166 --> 22:39.000
I'll take care of it.

22:39.000 --> 22:42.792
The church talks to the cops,
and the cops look into it...

22:42.792 --> 22:44.250
What's he got?

22:44.250 --> 22:45.750
Something Bunchy told him.
That's it.

22:45.750 --> 22:47.375
You know how many
Catholic cops there are?

22:47.375 --> 22:49.125
You don't think someone
high up in the church

22:49.125 --> 22:50.750
isn't gonna call one of them
to get his way?

22:50.750 --> 22:52.500
That is not the play.
He wouldn't have called me--

22:52.500 --> 22:53.959
Well, the play sure as hell
ain't asking you

22:53.959 --> 22:55.625
to say a Hail Mary.

22:55.625 --> 22:58.083
- I'm going by myself.
- No, you're not.

22:58.083 --> 22:59.834
Sit the fuck down, Bunch,
all right?

22:59.834 --> 23:01.667
[Bunchy] I know him.
I can talk to him, guys.

23:01.667 --> 23:04.083
[Ray]
You're not talking to anyone.

23:04.083 --> 23:05.709
You're gonna keep
your fucking mouth shut.

23:05.709 --> 23:09.333
You understand me, huh?

23:09.333 --> 23:12.417
You're in over
your fucking head, Bunch.

23:13.917 --> 23:16.667
It's the truth,
and you fucking know it.

23:20.458 --> 23:24.709
I know you two think
that I'm not smart...

23:27.208 --> 23:30.166
...that I'm weak,

23:30.166 --> 23:32.917
but it ain't true.

23:38.250 --> 23:41.333
Look, Bunch...

23:41.333 --> 23:46.208
I can't help it
if people lie

23:46.208 --> 23:50.583
and cheat and do bad things.

23:54.959 --> 23:58.542
I never hurt nobody.

24:00.000 --> 24:02.083
I know, Bunch.

24:08.208 --> 24:10.375
- Brendan.
- I can't.

24:15.208 --> 24:17.041
Hey.

24:17.041 --> 24:19.291
You don't treat him like that.
He's not a boy.

24:21.959 --> 24:23.917
Stay out of this.

24:23.917 --> 24:26.041
Maybe he'd act more grown up
if you didn't treat him

24:26.041 --> 24:28.125
like a fucking baby.

24:28.125 --> 24:29.417
Mind your business.

24:29.417 --> 24:32.166
Brendan is
my fucking business.

24:32.166 --> 24:35.417
We're in love.
You better get used to me.

24:35.417 --> 24:38.542
[hip-hop music plays
on stereo]

24:38.542 --> 24:43.625
♪♪♪

24:49.875 --> 24:52.083
I'm coming.

24:52.083 --> 24:53.375
Stay here.

24:53.375 --> 24:58.250
I'm not letting you
go alone.

24:58.250 --> 25:01.083
[light guitar music playing]

25:01.083 --> 25:06.208
♪♪♪

25:40.333 --> 25:42.291
Have you been drinking,
Bridge?

25:42.291 --> 25:45.291
No, I had a friend come over,
and she went into the liquor.

25:45.291 --> 25:47.834
[scoffs]
Jesus fucking Christ.

25:47.834 --> 25:50.417
No, I wasn't drinking.
She was.

25:53.291 --> 25:57.250
Things I did
when I was your age,

25:57.250 --> 25:59.208
I don't even want
to fucking tell you.

25:59.208 --> 26:01.834
[laughs]

26:01.834 --> 26:03.333
[sighs]

26:08.542 --> 26:11.792
Why'd you, uh,
why'd you choose Dad?

26:11.792 --> 26:15.667
[laughs]

26:15.667 --> 26:19.500
I always understood him,
and he understood me.

26:19.500 --> 26:21.500
We had each other's back.

26:24.000 --> 26:27.709
What if--I don't know--
what if Daddy hadn't liked you?

26:27.709 --> 26:29.917
Would you still have
gone after him?

26:29.917 --> 26:32.542
Is there someone you like,
Bridge?

26:32.542 --> 26:35.000
Someone you want
to go after?

26:35.000 --> 26:38.542
Yeah,
but he's sort of aloof.

26:38.542 --> 26:42.041
That's just teenage bullshit.
It's a pose.

26:42.041 --> 26:45.625
Of course
he fucking likes you.

26:45.625 --> 26:48.291
You should make a move.
Show me his picture.

26:48.291 --> 26:52.166
No, no, he's, um,
he's not on Facebook.

26:52.166 --> 26:53.250
Okay.

26:54.792 --> 26:56.000
I should get back to this.

26:56.000 --> 26:57.417
All right.

26:59.208 --> 27:00.625
I love you,
sweetheart.

27:03.875 --> 27:06.542
- No more of this for you.
- [laughs]

27:09.458 --> 27:11.291
[sighs]

27:29.417 --> 27:31.500
That was stupid.

27:47.458 --> 27:49.083
[sighs]

27:49.083 --> 27:50.333
I spoke to Abby.

27:50.333 --> 27:52.709
We're gonna give you
the guest room.

27:52.709 --> 27:54.250
What?

27:54.250 --> 27:56.000
You're moving in
with us, Terry.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.625
I'm not moving
into your house.

27:57.625 --> 27:59.542
Did you hear what the doctor
said this morning?

28:03.542 --> 28:06.500
You remember when Bunchy used to
hide those girl superhero comics

28:06.500 --> 28:09.792
in his room,
like they were Playboys?

28:11.500 --> 28:13.125
What made you think of that?

28:13.125 --> 28:17.125
He's been looking for a woman
like that all his life.

28:17.125 --> 28:19.500
It's like that Mexican girl
of his just walked out

28:19.500 --> 28:21.792
of one of those comic books.

28:29.291 --> 28:33.750
Move in with us, Terry.

28:33.750 --> 28:37.000
I'll think about it.

28:45.458 --> 28:47.166
Hey, yo, Pop,
you ready?

28:47.166 --> 28:48.750
Yeah.

28:53.458 --> 28:55.750
Hey, to what do
we owe this pleasure?

28:57.000 --> 28:59.875
I'm getting married, Pop.

28:59.875 --> 29:01.125
Holy shit.

29:01.125 --> 29:03.083
Her name is Teresa,

29:03.083 --> 29:06.333
and she's
a Mexican-American luchadora.

29:06.333 --> 29:08.542
[laughs]

29:08.542 --> 29:11.375
My baby boy

29:11.375 --> 29:14.750
is gonna tie the knot, huh?

29:14.750 --> 29:16.041
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

29:16.041 --> 29:18.208
I'm your youngest son,
though, Pop.

29:18.208 --> 29:20.834
From a proper marriage
is all I'm saying.

29:20.834 --> 29:22.875
- Wow.
- What a fucking mitzvah, huh?

29:22.875 --> 29:26.959
Here, let's have a drink,
celebrate here.

29:28.166 --> 29:29.375
D.

29:29.375 --> 29:32.083
I ain't drinking.

29:32.083 --> 29:34.959
Well, here's to you.

29:36.208 --> 29:37.250
Is something wrong?

29:37.250 --> 29:40.834
I got someone to support now,

29:40.834 --> 29:43.208
and Ray won't give me
my settlement money.

29:43.208 --> 29:44.542
Oh, he won't, huh?

29:44.542 --> 29:46.583
[Bunchy]
I'm tired of this shit.

29:48.375 --> 29:51.709
I was wondering if I could come
do some more work for you.

29:54.500 --> 29:58.250
Well, you come
at a very auspicious moment.

29:58.250 --> 30:00.250
- I have?
- We're doing a big negotiation.

30:00.250 --> 30:03.917
And I can certainly use
an extra hand.

30:13.166 --> 30:16.250
[soft piano music playing]

30:16.250 --> 30:18.250
♪♪♪

30:18.250 --> 30:19.959
[buzzer]

30:22.792 --> 30:25.959
You ever blame me
for O'Connor?

30:28.375 --> 30:31.500
Why would you say that?

30:31.500 --> 30:35.417
I heard you crying
some nights.

30:35.417 --> 30:38.375
I knew what you
were crying about.

30:47.834 --> 30:49.542
What are we gonna do
with this guy?

30:49.542 --> 30:52.041
We  are not doing anything.

31:01.458 --> 31:03.667
[Terry]
I'm coming with you.

31:03.667 --> 31:06.959
No, you're not.
Stay here.

31:08.500 --> 31:10.250
[car door closes]

31:10.250 --> 31:11.709
[door opens]

31:17.583 --> 31:20.458
Mr. Donovan,
I'm Thomas Romero.

31:20.458 --> 31:21.875
What do you want?

31:21.875 --> 31:24.125
I need to talk to you
about Father O'Connor.

31:24.125 --> 31:25.917
I can't help you there.

31:25.917 --> 31:28.333
You wouldn't have come this far
if what your brother told me

31:28.333 --> 31:30.875
wasn't true.

31:30.875 --> 31:32.917
Please.

31:52.500 --> 31:54.583
You afraid of driving fast?

31:55.709 --> 31:58.750
No.

31:58.750 --> 32:00.834
Slide over behind
the steering wheel.

32:00.834 --> 32:02.959
Keep the car running.

32:15.875 --> 32:18.333
Yeah,
the old pistol-whip thing,

32:18.333 --> 32:20.041
that's some bitch shit, man.

32:20.041 --> 32:23.166
- I like the suit.
- Thank you.

32:23.166 --> 32:25.417
You got the money?

32:25.417 --> 32:27.625
I do.

32:27.625 --> 32:31.333
You gonna give my son
his car back?

32:31.333 --> 32:33.041
Keys.

32:36.125 --> 32:38.291
Get out of here.

32:38.291 --> 32:39.917
Hey, what the fuck is this,
funny money?

32:39.917 --> 32:42.375
You want my business,
here's my business.

32:42.375 --> 32:44.250
[both grunting]

32:55.583 --> 32:57.792
Ohh.

32:58.792 --> 33:00.500
[whimpers]

33:01.750 --> 33:04.834
[breathing heavily]

33:14.375 --> 33:17.417
[groans]

33:19.500 --> 33:22.250
Ahh! Ahh!

33:22.250 --> 33:23.542
[screams]

33:23.542 --> 33:25.125
Bunch, Bunch, stop.

33:25.125 --> 33:27.125
Bunch, stop.
Stop, stop, stop.

33:27.125 --> 33:29.000
He's down.
He's down, all right?

33:29.000 --> 33:30.542
Be cool.
Chill, chill, chill.

33:30.542 --> 33:32.583
Listen, listen, listen,
get Pop home, all right?

33:32.583 --> 33:34.959
Let's get out of here.

33:34.959 --> 33:37.667
Get Pop out.
I'm right behind you.

33:41.333 --> 33:44.208
[tires squealing]

33:52.542 --> 33:54.125
I was sent here under orders
from the Vatican

33:54.125 --> 33:56.458
to put a system in place
for treating priests

33:56.458 --> 33:58.083
who had sinned
against children.

33:58.083 --> 34:00.917
I brought in
psychiatric professionals,

34:00.917 --> 34:03.166
created a place
of vocational renewal

34:03.166 --> 34:06.000
built in the spirit
of healing and hope.

34:07.792 --> 34:09.166
Good night, Father Romero.

34:09.166 --> 34:11.041
Good night, Anthony.

34:11.041 --> 34:13.500
God bless.

34:13.500 --> 34:17.500
[indistinct chatter]

34:17.500 --> 34:20.166
[coughs]

34:21.834 --> 34:23.750
Pray that when you see
a priest beaten down,

34:23.750 --> 34:25.000
you see in him Jesus.

34:25.000 --> 34:28.667
You mean like Father O'Connor?

34:28.667 --> 34:31.625
Father O'Connor left
a trail of wreckage.

34:31.625 --> 34:35.250
It's true,
but over many years,

34:35.250 --> 34:37.000
he worked through
what he did.

34:37.000 --> 34:38.750
- He took responsibility.
- Don't kid yourself.

34:38.750 --> 34:41.792
He went through
a full disclosure.

34:41.792 --> 34:44.667
Told me
all about your brother.

34:44.667 --> 34:47.041
Told me all about you.

34:47.041 --> 34:51.875
What's that
supposed to mean, huh?

34:51.875 --> 34:53.792
[laughs]

34:55.834 --> 34:59.333
- What did he tell you about me?
- Everything.

34:59.333 --> 35:02.208
[clock ticking]

35:06.375 --> 35:08.458
No, I didn't bring you here
to threaten you,

35:08.458 --> 35:09.709
Mr. Donovan, trust me.

35:09.709 --> 35:12.917
Why,
because you're a priest?

35:12.917 --> 35:16.667
You already lied
to my brother.

35:16.667 --> 35:17.834
What the fuck
do you want?

35:17.834 --> 35:19.375
After he left the Paraclete,

35:19.375 --> 35:21.208
Father O'Connor and I
spoke twice a day,

35:21.208 --> 35:22.583
in the morning
when he woke up

35:22.583 --> 35:23.875
and the evening
before he went to sleep.

35:23.875 --> 35:25.417
Then he disappeared.

35:25.417 --> 35:27.375
I figured I'd made a grave error
in letting him go,

35:27.375 --> 35:29.458
that he'd returned
to his former ways.

35:29.458 --> 35:31.000
Then his body was found,

35:31.000 --> 35:32.750
and I knew his past
had caught up with him.

35:32.750 --> 35:34.500
Yeah, well, you know,
like I said,

35:34.500 --> 35:36.041
I can't help you there.

35:36.041 --> 35:40.000
You hated him,
and for good reason.

35:40.000 --> 35:41.709
He did to you the worst thing

35:41.709 --> 35:45.375
a man could do to a child,

35:45.375 --> 35:48.000
but he atoned.

35:48.000 --> 35:52.417
He devoted himself
to his recovery and to Christ.

35:52.417 --> 35:54.250
He tried to make amends
every day

35:54.250 --> 35:55.625
through his life
and his work.

35:55.625 --> 35:57.208
He wasn't innocent.

35:57.208 --> 36:00.250
He wasn't innocent,
not when he hurt you,

36:00.250 --> 36:02.417
but he was innocent
when you killed him.

36:12.375 --> 36:15.625
You got nothing.

36:15.625 --> 36:17.959
A conversation
with my alcoholic brother.

36:17.959 --> 36:19.000
You're not listening to me.

36:19.000 --> 36:21.375
I have everything you need.

36:24.083 --> 36:26.750
Yeah?

36:26.750 --> 36:29.208
What do I need?

36:31.125 --> 36:33.125
Forgiveness.

36:34.959 --> 36:38.125
I want to forgive you.

36:41.166 --> 36:43.417
Admit what you did.

36:43.417 --> 36:47.875
Come with me right now
to the chapel and confess.

36:49.417 --> 36:52.291
Accept God,

36:52.291 --> 36:54.000
and you and I
will forget everything

36:54.000 --> 36:58.208
that came before this.

37:09.458 --> 37:13.166
You're saying I confess,
and you don't go to the cops.

37:13.166 --> 37:17.333
Admit what you did,

37:17.333 --> 37:20.500
why you did it,

37:20.500 --> 37:24.000
repent,

37:24.000 --> 37:26.792
and all will be forgiven.

37:26.792 --> 37:29.834
[soft music playing]

37:29.834 --> 37:34.959
♪♪♪

37:51.375 --> 37:55.834
When's the last time
you were in church?

37:55.834 --> 37:58.250
I don't remember.

38:02.166 --> 38:04.875
I've been where you
and your brother were.

38:04.875 --> 38:09.250
I had violence
in my heart.

38:09.250 --> 38:12.417
What's that
supposed to mean?

38:12.417 --> 38:15.917
I didn't deceive
your brother Brendan.

38:15.917 --> 38:18.083
I told him the truth.

38:18.083 --> 38:19.667
I told him my story,

38:19.667 --> 38:23.125
and that's why
he told me yours.

38:24.875 --> 38:28.959
You can trust me.

38:28.959 --> 38:33.583
Trust that the seal
of confession is absolute.

38:40.417 --> 38:44.583
All you've got to do
is ask Him, Ray.

38:44.583 --> 38:47.792
Let Him teach you
to forgive.

39:18.000 --> 39:19.792
[exhales]

39:35.834 --> 39:39.000
Forgive me, Father,
for I have sinned.

39:41.875 --> 39:44.709
It's, uh...

39:47.458 --> 39:50.875
...been 36 years
since my last confession.

39:54.166 --> 39:57.500
I...

40:03.166 --> 40:04.667
Wait, Ray.
Don't go.

40:04.667 --> 40:08.458
Ray, prison will not help you
or your brother, only God will.

40:08.458 --> 40:09.375
- You got nothing.
- You believe, Ray.

40:09.375 --> 40:11.000
I know you do.

40:11.000 --> 40:12.417
You would not have hesitated
at the door of the confessional

40:12.417 --> 40:14.375
if you didn't;
don't walk away from this.

40:14.375 --> 40:15.458
Repent.

40:15.458 --> 40:17.000
Repent now
or face excommunication.

40:17.000 --> 40:18.291
What?

40:18.291 --> 40:20.208
Repent now
or face excommunication.

40:20.208 --> 40:21.792
[Ray]
I'm the sinner?

40:21.792 --> 40:23.875
You hide and protect these men
who should be dead or in prison,

40:23.875 --> 40:25.125
and I'm the fucking sinner?

40:25.125 --> 40:26.291
- I know you feel hate.
- Fuck you.

40:26.291 --> 40:27.709
I know how badly
he hurt you,

40:27.709 --> 40:29.458
and I know how much
you loved him.

40:29.458 --> 40:31.208
[grunting]

40:32.333 --> 40:33.959
I'll fucking kill you.

40:33.959 --> 40:35.709
Fuck you!

40:35.709 --> 40:37.458
I'll kill you and every one
of these fucking freaks

40:37.458 --> 40:39.375
you got hiding in here.

40:39.375 --> 40:42.542
[Thomas speaking Latin]

40:46.709 --> 40:48.750
In the name of God,
the all powerful Father,

40:48.750 --> 40:51.542
Son, and Holy Ghost,
and all of the saints,

40:51.542 --> 40:52.917
I deprive you
of the Communion

40:52.917 --> 40:54.208
of the Body and Blood
of Our Lord...

40:54.208 --> 40:56.875
You think
I fucking care, huh?

40:56.875 --> 40:58.959
You think
I need your fucking church?

40:58.959 --> 41:00.375
And anathematized.

41:00.375 --> 41:01.917
I judge you...

41:01.917 --> 41:03.667
What did you do
for my sister, my mother?

41:03.667 --> 41:05.333
Burst the fetters
of the demon.

41:05.333 --> 41:06.750
What did your church
ever do for me, huh?

41:06.750 --> 41:08.208
- Fuck you! Fuck you!
- [speaking Latin]

41:08.208 --> 41:10.000
And fuck your forgiveness!

41:10.000 --> 41:12.083
Fiat in die judicii.

41:12.083 --> 41:13.917
Fiat. Fiat.

41:13.917 --> 41:15.500
Fiat.

41:15.500 --> 41:17.250
Repent.

41:17.250 --> 41:19.417
Let me help you.

41:19.417 --> 41:21.917
- Okay.
- Come on, Pop.

41:21.917 --> 41:23.417
Come here.

41:23.417 --> 41:25.542
Let's get you
sitting down here.

41:25.542 --> 41:28.417
- You all right?
- Don't touch me there.

41:28.417 --> 41:30.166
That's it.

41:35.083 --> 41:36.917
You gonna be okay?

41:36.917 --> 41:38.583
I'm fine.

41:38.583 --> 41:41.583
That was nothing.

41:43.792 --> 41:45.625
[exhales]

41:45.625 --> 41:47.625
You do know they're gonna
come after us, right?

41:49.250 --> 41:52.208
Sometimes you've got to
push back to get some respect.

41:54.417 --> 41:57.166
They are going
to come after us.

42:02.667 --> 42:04.625
My fucking suit
is ruined.

42:10.041 --> 42:12.458
I got to get back
to my girl.

42:24.458 --> 42:28.500
You were a lion
out there tonight,

42:28.500 --> 42:30.250
a fucking lion.

42:36.333 --> 42:39.166
[light guitar music playing]

42:39.166 --> 42:44.250
♪♪♪

42:55.959 --> 43:00.166
♪ Strange things are happening ♪

43:00.166 --> 43:01.917
♪ Every day ♪

43:01.917 --> 43:04.250
♪ I hear the music ♪

43:04.250 --> 43:07.959
♪ Up above my head ♪

43:07.959 --> 43:11.208
♪ Though the sight
Of my heart ♪

43:11.208 --> 43:12.667
He excommunicated us.

43:12.667 --> 43:15.959
[Bridget]
♪ Has left me again ♪

43:15.959 --> 43:17.333
Me.

43:17.333 --> 43:19.875
No, he said "accomplices."

43:21.125 --> 43:22.667
He didn't mean you.

43:22.667 --> 43:24.542
Yes, he did.

43:24.542 --> 43:28.542
He meant me,
and he meant Bunchy.

43:32.458 --> 43:34.709
You didn't do anything, Terry.

43:37.959 --> 43:40.625
We killed a priest.

43:42.417 --> 43:45.250
[Bridget]
♪ Secrets are written ♪

43:45.250 --> 43:47.834
♪ In the sky ♪

43:47.834 --> 43:51.083
♪ Looks like
I've lost the love ♪

43:51.083 --> 43:54.542
♪ I've never found ♪

43:54.542 --> 43:58.417
♪ Though the sound of hope ♪

43:58.417 --> 44:01.208
♪ Has left me again ♪

44:01.208 --> 44:05.250
♪ I hear music up above ♪

44:05.250 --> 44:06.917
Get your stuff.

44:06.917 --> 44:10.583
What are we gonna do
about the priest, Ray?

44:10.583 --> 44:12.208
I don't know.

44:12.208 --> 44:13.750
You don't know?

44:13.750 --> 44:15.583
I don't fucking know, Terry.

44:15.583 --> 44:18.083
I got to think about it.

44:18.083 --> 44:20.583
Right now,
I don't know.

44:25.208 --> 44:28.208
Get your stuff.

44:28.208 --> 44:29.917
You tell Abby
I appreciate the offer,

44:29.917 --> 44:31.417
but I can't move in with you.

44:31.417 --> 44:33.125
You don't have a choice, Ter.

44:33.125 --> 44:35.125
You got a lot going on
in your life, Ray.

44:35.125 --> 44:37.000
You don't need no more.

44:42.417 --> 44:43.959
Don't worry
about what I need.

44:43.959 --> 44:46.959
You need your family,
your  family.

44:46.959 --> 44:49.458
The rest of us
are lost causes.

44:55.792 --> 44:59.000
[Bridget]
♪ I hear Rosetta singing ♪

44:59.000 --> 45:00.709
♪ In the night ♪

45:00.709 --> 45:04.250
♪ Echoes of light
That shine like stars ♪

45:04.250 --> 45:07.625
♪ After they're gone ♪

45:07.625 --> 45:11.333
♪ And tonight she's my guide ♪

45:11.333 --> 45:14.041
♪ As I go out alone ♪

45:14.041 --> 45:18.333
♪ With the music ♪

45:18.333 --> 45:22.500
♪ Up above ♪

45:27.834 --> 45:30.709
[phone chimes]

45:39.166 --> 45:41.583
[phone chimes]

45:47.500 --> 45:52.333
[phone rings]

45:52.333 --> 45:53.792
- Yeah.
- Where have you been?

45:53.792 --> 45:55.750
- Something came up.
- I was worried.

45:55.750 --> 45:57.625
I'm fine.
I'll call you in the morning.

45:57.625 --> 46:01.125
I need you to come
to my house now.

46:01.125 --> 46:02.875
Paige--

46:02.875 --> 46:04.458
I figured out
how to handle Napier.

46:04.458 --> 46:05.875
It's going to work out
for everyone,

46:05.875 --> 46:09.208
but I need you to come now.

46:13.583 --> 46:16.542
[dog barking in the distance]

46:24.959 --> 46:28.250
[phone rings]

46:28.250 --> 46:29.375
Hey, Ray.

46:29.375 --> 46:30.542
I'm gonna be late.

46:30.542 --> 46:32.000
The room's almost ready.

46:32.000 --> 46:33.583
Looks fucking great.

46:33.583 --> 46:35.500
Yeah?

46:35.500 --> 46:38.875
Terry says he, uh,
doesn't want to move in.

46:38.875 --> 46:40.625
- Is he okay?
- He's fine.

46:40.625 --> 46:43.417
He just says he doesn't want
to move in anymore.

46:43.417 --> 46:45.291
Are you okay?

46:45.291 --> 46:47.041
[sighs]

46:47.041 --> 46:49.834
I'm sorry I put you through
all that trouble.

46:49.834 --> 46:53.083
It's all right.
Maybe he'll change his mind.

46:53.083 --> 46:56.417
I don't know about that.

46:56.417 --> 46:58.291
So where are you?

47:00.375 --> 47:03.208
I got work.

47:03.208 --> 47:05.625
Okay, Ray.

47:08.583 --> 47:11.625
[sighs]

47:14.625 --> 47:16.500
[doorbell chimes]

47:33.125 --> 47:35.291
In hindsight, my marriage
was good for everyone.

47:35.291 --> 47:37.625
My dad got to be
around Varick,

47:37.625 --> 47:39.709
and I got my dad's attention.

47:39.709 --> 47:41.333
[liquid pours]

47:43.083 --> 47:44.625
Drink?

47:44.625 --> 47:47.959
You called about the deal,
said you figured it out.

47:55.208 --> 47:56.333
I lied.

48:00.834 --> 48:03.417
- I got to go.
- Why?

48:06.166 --> 48:08.500
I don't know
many men like you.

48:08.500 --> 48:10.041
Sure you do.

48:10.041 --> 48:12.125
No, the men I know
want money and power,

48:12.125 --> 48:14.959
but you don't give a fuck
about those things.

48:14.959 --> 48:18.458
You don't care
about houses or cars.

48:18.458 --> 48:20.959
How do you know?

48:20.959 --> 48:24.583
Because you're addicted
to the fight.

48:28.500 --> 48:30.250
I got to go, Paige.

48:30.250 --> 48:32.166
No, you don't.

48:32.166 --> 48:35.250
[tense music playing]

48:35.250 --> 48:40.125
♪♪♪

48:52.417 --> 48:57.250
♪♪♪
